In 1994, Prince Charles admitted to infidelity after his marriage to Princess Diana had broken down.
Despite opposition from some Anglicans, Charles and Camilla Parker Bowles, both divorcees, will marry in a civil ceremony at Windsor Castle.
Prime Minister Tony Blair expressed his delight and well wishes for the couple.
The Archbishop of Canterbury welcomed the news, emphasizing support for their decision.
The public reaction was mixed, with many welcoming the announcement while others still hold Princess Diana in high regard.
The couple's enduring relationship has garnered both admiration and controversy, marking a new chapter in their love story.
